The paper discusses cross-collection topic modeling, which is a common technique in natural language processing and information retrieval. The paper also mentions the evaluation of the model on patents, scientific papers, newspaper articles, forum posts, and Wikipedia articles, indicating a broad range of applications. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and information retrieval. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Deep Learning), which are all relevant to the topic of the paper.
